{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":750,"text":"So, security is two different things:"},{"time":3050,"text":"it's a feeling, and it's a reality."},{"time":5600,"text":"And they're different."},{"time":7049,"text":"You could feel secure even if you're not."},{"time":10500,"text":"And you can be secure"},{"time":12500,"text":"even if you don't feel it."},{"time":14374,"text":"Really, we have two separate concepts"},{"time":16515,"text":"mapped onto the same word."},{"time":18700,"text":"And what I want to do in this talk\nis to split them apart --"},{"time":22350,"text":"figuring out when they diverge\nand how they converge."},{"time":26451,"text":"And language is actually a problem here."},{"time":28750,"text":"There aren't a lot of good words"},{"time":30850,"text":"for the concepts\nwe're going to talk about."},{"time":34035,"text":"So if you look at security\nfrom economic terms,"},{"time":38179,"text":"it's a trade-off."}]},{"cues":[{"time":39850,"text":"Every time you get some security,\nyou're always trading off something."},{"time":44006,"text":"Whether this is a personal decision --"},{"time":45875,"text":"whether you're going to install\na burglar alarm in your home --"},{"time":48911,"text":"or a national decision,"},{"time":50092,"text":"where you're going to invade\na foreign country --"},{"time":52426,"text":"you're going to trade off something:\nmoney or time, convenience, capabilities,"},{"time":56232,"text":"maybe fundamental liberties."},{"time":58258,"text":"And the question to ask\nwhen you look at a security anything"},{"time":61556,"text":"is not whether this makes us safer,"},{"time":64962,"text":"but whether it's worth the trade-off."},{"time":67201,"text":"You've heard in the past\nseveral years, the world is safer"},{"time":70454,"text":"because Saddam Hussein is not in power."},{"time":72368,"text":"That might be true,\nbut it's not terribly relevant."},{"time":74995,"text":"The question is: Was it worth it?"},{"time":77850,"text":"And you can make your own decision,"},{"time":80333,"text":"and then you'll decide\nwhether the invasion was worth it."},{"time":83090,"text":"That's how you think about security:\nin terms of the trade-off."}]},{"cues":[{"time":86675,"text":"Now, there's often no right or wrong here."},{"time":89948,"text":"Some of us have a burglar alarm\nsystem at home and some of us don't."},{"time":93280,"text":"And it'll depend on where we live,"},{"time":96035,"text":"whether we live alone or have a family,"},{"time":97985,"text":"how much cool stuff we have,"},{"time":99677,"text":"how much we're willing\nto accept the risk of theft."},{"time":103683,"text":"In politics also,\nthere are different opinions."},{"time":107199,"text":"A lot of times, these trade-offs\nare about more than just security,"},{"time":111658,"text":"and I think that's really important."},{"time":113547,"text":"Now, people have a natural intuition\nabout these trade-offs."},{"time":117328,"text":"We make them every day."},{"time":119547,"text":"Last night in my hotel room,\nwhen I decided to double-lock the door,"},{"time":123104,"text":"or you in your car when you drove here;"},{"time":125931,"text":"when we go eat lunch"},{"time":127433,"text":"and decide the food's not\npoison and we'll eat it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":130065,"text":"We make these trade-offs again and again,"},{"time":133250,"text":"multiple times a day."},{"time":134850,"text":"We often won't even notice them."},{"time":136463,"text":"They're just part\nof being alive; we all do it."},{"time":139113,"text":"Every species does it."},{"time":141214,"text":"Imagine a rabbit in a field, eating grass."},{"time":144100,"text":"And the rabbit sees a fox."},{"time":146596,"text":"That rabbit will make\na security trade-off:"},{"time":148669,"text":"\"Should I stay, or should I flee?\""},{"time":151120,"text":"And if you think about it,"},{"time":152763,"text":"the rabbits that are good\nat making that trade-off"},{"time":155342,"text":"will tend to live and reproduce,"},{"time":157344,"text":"and the rabbits that are bad at it"},{"time":159675,"text":"will get eaten or starve."},{"time":161698,"text":"So you'd think"},{"time":164313,"text":"that us, as a successful species\non the planet -- you, me, everybody --"},{"time":168646,"text":"would be really good\nat making these trade-offs."},{"time":171866,"text":"Yet it seems, again and again,\nthat we're hopelessly bad at it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":176508,"text":"And I think that's a fundamentally\ninteresting question."},{"time":179334,"text":"I'll give you the short answer."},{"time":181231,"text":"The answer is, we respond\nto the feeling of security"},{"time":183906,"text":"and not the reality."},{"time":186604,"text":"Now, most of the time, that works."},{"time":190278,"text":"Most of the time,"},{"time":191805,"text":"feeling and reality are the same."},{"time":195516,"text":"Certainly that's true\nfor most of human prehistory."},{"time":200373,"text":"We've developed this ability"},{"time":203105,"text":"because it makes evolutionary sense."},{"time":206725,"text":"One way to think of it\nis that we're highly optimized"},{"time":210023,"text":"for risk decisions"},{"time":211850,"text":"that are endemic to living\nin small family groups"},{"time":214417,"text":"in the East African Highlands\nin 100,000 BC."},{"time":217532,"text":"2010 New York, not so much."},{"time":221619,"text":"Now, there are several biases\nin risk perception."},{"time":224849,"text":"A lot of good experiments in this."},{"time":226614,"text":"And you can see certain biases\nthat come up again and again."},{"time":230241,"text":"I'll give you four."}]},{"cues":[{"time":231618,"text":"We tend to exaggerate\nspectacular and rare risks"},{"time":234850,"text":"and downplay common risks --"},{"time":236850,"text":"so, flying versus driving."},{"time":239191,"text":"The unknown is perceived\nto be riskier than the familiar."},{"time":246210,"text":"One example would be:"},{"time":247673,"text":"people fear kidnapping by strangers,"},{"time":250310,"text":"when the data supports that kidnapping\nby relatives is much more common."},{"time":253970,"text":"This is for children."},{"time":255568,"text":"Third, personified risks\nare perceived to be greater"},{"time":259632,"text":"than anonymous risks."},{"time":261159,"text":"So, Bin Laden is scarier\nbecause he has a name."},{"time":264922,"text":"And the fourth is:"},{"time":266309,"text":"people underestimate risks\nin situations they do control"},{"time":271088,"text":"and overestimate them\nin situations they don't control."},{"time":274075,"text":"So once you take up skydiving or smoking,"},{"time":277483,"text":"you downplay the risks."},{"time":279777,"text":"If a risk is thrust upon you --\nterrorism is a good example --"},{"time":282854,"text":"you'll overplay it,"},{"time":284035,"text":"because you don't feel\nlike it's in your control."}]},{"cues":[{"time":286897,"text":"There are a bunch\nof other of these cognitive biases,"},{"time":290414,"text":"that affect our risk decisions."},{"time":293572,"text":"There's the availability heuristic,"},{"time":295850,"text":"which basically means we estimate\nthe probability of something"},{"time":300054,"text":"by how easy it is to bring\ninstances of it to mind."},{"time":304571,"text":"So you can imagine how that works."},{"time":306372,"text":"If you hear a lot about tiger attacks,\nthere must be a lot of tigers around."},{"time":310024,"text":"You don't hear about lion attacks,\nthere aren't a lot of lions around."},{"time":313392,"text":"This works, until you invent newspapers,"},{"time":315713,"text":"because what newspapers do\nis repeat again and again"},{"time":320143,"text":"rare risks."},{"time":321573,"text":"I tell people: if it's in the news,\ndon't worry about it,"},{"time":324462,"text":"because by definition, news is something\nthat almost never happens."}]},{"cues":[{"time":328761,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":330554,"text":"When something is so common,\nit's no longer news."},{"time":333501,"text":"Car crashes, domestic violence --"},{"time":335723,"text":"those are the risks you worry about."},{"time":338453,"text":"We're also a species of storytellers."},{"time":340625,"text":"We respond to stories more than data."},{"time":343254,"text":"And there's some basic\ninnumeracy going on."},{"time":345684,"text":"I mean, the joke \"One, two,\nthree, many\" is kind of right."},{"time":348850,"text":"We're really good at small numbers."},{"time":351196,"text":"One mango, two mangoes, three mangoes,"},{"time":353556,"text":"10,000 mangoes, 100,000 mangoes --"},{"time":355557,"text":"it's still more mangoes\nyou can eat before they rot."},{"time":358558,"text":"So one half, one quarter,\none fifth -- we're good at that."},{"time":361850,"text":"One in a million, one in a billion --"},{"time":363850,"text":"they're both almost never."}]},{"cues":[{"time":366286,"text":"So we have trouble with the risks\nthat aren't very common."},{"time":370500,"text":"And what these cognitive biases do"},{"time":372501,"text":"is they act as filters\nbetween us and reality."},{"time":376024,"text":"And the result is that feeling\nand reality get out of whack,"},{"time":379921,"text":"they get different."},{"time":382110,"text":"Now, you either have a feeling --\nyou feel more secure than you are,"},{"time":386065,"text":"there's a false sense of security."},{"time":387774,"text":"Or the other way, and that's a false\nsense of insecurity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":391755,"text":"I write a lot about \"security theater,\""},{"time":394659,"text":"which are products\nthat make people feel secure,"},{"time":397363,"text":"but don't actually do anything."},{"time":399364,"text":"There's no real word for stuff\nthat makes us secure,"},{"time":401945,"text":"but doesn't make us feel secure."},{"time":403850,"text":"Maybe it's what the CIA\nis supposed to do for us."},{"time":408279,"text":"So back to economics."},{"time":410471,"text":"If economics, if the market,\ndrives security,"},{"time":414151,"text":"and if people make trade-offs\nbased on the feeling of security,"},{"time":419022,"text":"then the smart thing for companies to do\nfor the economic incentives"},{"time":423726,"text":"is to make people feel secure."},{"time":426682,"text":"And there are two ways to do this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":429036,"text":"One, you can make people actually secure"},{"time":431850,"text":"and hope they notice."},{"time":433337,"text":"Or two, you can make people\njust feel secure"},{"time":436205,"text":"and hope they don't notice."},{"time":439141,"text":"Right?"},{"time":440540,"text":"So what makes people notice?"},{"time":444240,"text":"Well, a couple of things:"},{"time":445646,"text":"understanding of the security,"},{"time":447936,"text":"of the risks, the threats,"},{"time":449850,"text":"the countermeasures, how they work."},{"time":451748,"text":"But if you know stuff, you're more likely"},{"time":454895,"text":"to have your feelings match reality."},{"time":457850,"text":"Enough real-world examples helps."},{"time":461019,"text":"We all know the crime rate\nin our neighborhood,"},{"time":463602,"text":"because we live there,\nand we get a feeling about it"},{"time":466427,"text":"that basically matches reality."},{"time":469778,"text":"Security theater is exposed"},{"time":472009,"text":"when it's obvious\nthat it's not working properly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":475949,"text":"OK. So what makes people not notice?"},{"time":479183,"text":"Well, a poor understanding."},{"time":481382,"text":"If you don't understand the risks,\nyou don't understand the costs,"},{"time":484550,"text":"you're likely to get the trade-off wrong,"},{"time":486731,"text":"and your feeling doesn't match reality."},{"time":489243,"text":"Not enough examples."},{"time":491619,"text":"There's an inherent problem\nwith low-probability events."},{"time":495659,"text":"If, for example, terrorism\nalmost never happens,"},{"time":499496,"text":"it's really hard to judge the efficacy\nof counter-terrorist measures."},{"time":505263,"text":"This is why you keep sacrificing virgins,"},{"time":508850,"text":"and why your unicorn defenses\nare working just great."},{"time":511549,"text":"There aren't enough examples of failures."},{"time":515849,"text":"Also, feelings that cloud the issues --"},{"time":518660,"text":"the cognitive biases I talked\nabout earlier: fears, folk beliefs --"},{"time":523467,"text":"basically, an inadequate model of reality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":528143,"text":"So let me complicate things."},{"time":530338,"text":"I have feeling and reality."},{"time":532339,"text":"I want to add a third element.\nI want to add \"model.\""},{"time":535579,"text":"Feeling and model are in our head,"},{"time":537953,"text":"reality is the outside world;\nit doesn't change, it's real."},{"time":542540,"text":"Feeling is based on our intuition,"},{"time":544778,"text":"model is based on reason."},{"time":547123,"text":"That's basically the difference."},{"time":549186,"text":"In a primitive and simple world,"},{"time":551187,"text":"there's really no reason for a model,"},{"time":554993,"text":"because feeling is close to reality."},{"time":557312,"text":"You don't need a model."},{"time":559336,"text":"But in a modern and complex world,"},{"time":562296,"text":"you need models to understand\na lot of the risks we face."}]},{"cues":[{"time":567102,"text":"There's no feeling about germs."},{"time":569850,"text":"You need a model to understand them."},{"time":572897,"text":"This model is an intelligent\nrepresentation of reality."},{"time":577151,"text":"It's, of course, limited\nby science, by technology."},{"time":582989,"text":"We couldn't have a germ theory of disease"},{"time":585339,"text":"before we invented\nthe microscope to see them."},{"time":589056,"text":"It's limited by our cognitive biases."},{"time":592850,"text":"But it has the ability\nto override our feelings."},{"time":596247,"text":"Where do we get these models?\nWe get them from others."},{"time":599375,"text":"We get them from religion,\nfrom culture, teachers, elders."}]},{"cues":[{"time":605038,"text":"A couple years ago,\nI was in South Africa on safari."},{"time":608488,"text":"The tracker I was with grew up\nin Kruger National Park."},{"time":611274,"text":"He had some very complex\nmodels of how to survive."},{"time":614540,"text":"And it depended on if you were attacked\nby a lion, leopard, rhino, or elephant --"},{"time":618477,"text":"and when you had to run away,\nwhen you couldn't run away,"},{"time":621235,"text":"when you had to climb a tree,\nwhen you could never climb a tree."},{"time":624342,"text":"I would have died in a day."},{"time":626900,"text":"But he was born there,\nand he understood how to survive."},{"time":631230,"text":"I was born in New York City."},{"time":632850,"text":"I could have taken him to New York,\nand he would have died in a day."}]},{"cues":[{"time":636125,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":637150,"text":"Because we had different models\nbased on our different experiences."},{"time":643031,"text":"Models can come from the media,"},{"time":645524,"text":"from our elected officials ..."},{"time":647974,"text":"Think of models of terrorism,"},{"time":651079,"text":"child kidnapping,"},{"time":653300,"text":"airline safety, car safety."},{"time":656279,"text":"Models can come from industry."},{"time":659088,"text":"The two I'm following\nare surveillance cameras,"},{"time":662330,"text":"ID cards,"},{"time":663850,"text":"quite a lot of our computer\nsecurity models come from there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":667004,"text":"A lot of models come from science."},{"time":669255,"text":"Health models are a great example."},{"time":671116,"text":"Think of cancer, bird flu,\nswine flu, SARS."},{"time":674682,"text":"All of our feelings of security\nabout those diseases"},{"time":679576,"text":"come from models given to us, really,\nby science filtered through the media."},{"time":685778,"text":"So models can change."},{"time":688222,"text":"Models are not static."},{"time":690349,"text":"As we become more comfortable\nin our environments,"},{"time":693613,"text":"our model can move closer to our feelings."}]},{"cues":[{"time":698705,"text":"So an example might be,"},{"time":701069,"text":"if you go back 100 years ago,"},{"time":702689,"text":"when electricity was first\nbecoming common,"},{"time":706141,"text":"there were a lot of fears about it."},{"time":707868,"text":"There were people who were afraid\nto push doorbells,"},{"time":710370,"text":"because there was electricity\nin there, and that was dangerous."},{"time":713399,"text":"For us, we're very facile\naround electricity."},{"time":716292,"text":"We change light bulbs\nwithout even thinking about it."},{"time":719688,"text":"Our model of security around electricity\nis something we were born into."},{"time":726475,"text":"It hasn't changed as we were growing up."},{"time":729013,"text":"And we're good at it."},{"time":732120,"text":"Or think of the risks on the Internet\nacross generations --"},{"time":736643,"text":"how your parents approach\nInternet security,"},{"time":738764,"text":"versus how you do,"},{"time":740404,"text":"versus how our kids will."}]},{"cues":[{"time":743040,"text":"Models eventually fade\ninto the background."},{"time":747167,"text":"\"Intuitive\" is just\nanother word for familiar."},{"time":750627,"text":"So as your model is close to reality\nand it converges with feelings,"},{"time":754501,"text":"you often don't even know it's there."},{"time":757979,"text":"A nice example of this came\nfrom last year and swine flu."},{"time":763021,"text":"When swine flu first appeared,"},{"time":765045,"text":"the initial news caused\na lot of overreaction."},{"time":768302,"text":"Now, it had a name,"},{"time":770304,"text":"which made it scarier\nthan the regular flu,"},{"time":772378,"text":"even though it was more deadly."},{"time":774524,"text":"And people thought doctors\nshould be able to deal with it."},{"time":778199,"text":"So there was that feeling\nof lack of control."},{"time":780747,"text":"And those two things\nmade the risk more than it was."}]},{"cues":[{"time":783880,"text":"As the novelty wore off\nand the months went by,"},{"time":787461,"text":"there was some amount of tolerance;\npeople got used to it."},{"time":791095,"text":"There was no new data,\nbut there was less fear."},{"time":794421,"text":"By autumn,"},{"time":796619,"text":"people thought the doctors\nshould have solved this already."},{"time":800462,"text":"And there's kind of a bifurcation:"},{"time":802446,"text":"people had to choose\nbetween fear and acceptance --"},{"time":809252,"text":"actually, fear and indifference --"},{"time":810920,"text":"and they kind of chose suspicion."},{"time":813850,"text":"And when the vaccine appeared last winter,"},{"time":816985,"text":"there were a lot of people --\na surprising number --"},{"time":819520,"text":"who refused to get it."},{"time":823517,"text":"And it's a nice example of how\npeople's feelings of security change,"},{"time":827197,"text":"how their model changes,"},{"time":828824,"text":"sort of wildly,"},{"time":830516,"text":"with no new information,\nwith no new input."},{"time":835067,"text":"This kind of thing happens a lot."}]},{"cues":[{"time":837939,"text":"I'm going to give one more complication."},{"time":839934,"text":"We have feeling, model, reality."},{"time":843380,"text":"I have a very relativistic\nview of security."},{"time":845914,"text":"I think it depends on the observer."},{"time":848435,"text":"And most security decisions\nhave a variety of people involved."},{"time":854532,"text":"And stakeholders with specific trade-offs\nwill try to influence the decision."},{"time":861095,"text":"And I call that their agenda."},{"time":864252,"text":"And you see agenda --\nthis is marketing, this is politics --"},{"time":868221,"text":"trying to convince you to have\none model versus another,"},{"time":871284,"text":"trying to convince you to ignore a model"},{"time":873292,"text":"and trust your feelings,"},{"time":875988,"text":"marginalizing people\nwith models you don't like."},{"time":879484,"text":"This is not uncommon."},{"time":882350,"text":"An example, a great example,\nis the risk of smoking."},{"time":886936,"text":"In the history of the past 50 years,"},{"time":888743,"text":"the smoking risk shows\nhow a model changes,"},{"time":891380,"text":"and it also shows how an industry fights\nagainst a model it doesn't like."}]},{"cues":[{"time":896723,"text":"Compare that to the secondhand\nsmoke debate --"},{"time":899850,"text":"probably about 20 years behind."},{"time":902722,"text":"Think about seat belts."},{"time":904361,"text":"When I was a kid, no one wore a seat belt."},{"time":906409,"text":"Nowadays, no kid will let you drive\nif you're not wearing a seat belt."},{"time":911373,"text":"Compare that to the airbag debate,"},{"time":913850,"text":"probably about 30 years behind."},{"time":916746,"text":"All examples of models changing."},{"time":921595,"text":"What we learn is that changing\nmodels is hard."},{"time":925074,"text":"Models are hard to dislodge."},{"time":927151,"text":"If they equal your feelings,"},{"time":928850,"text":"you don't even know you have a model."},{"time":931850,"text":"And there's another cognitive bias"},{"time":933760,"text":"I'll call confirmation bias,"},{"time":935850,"text":"where we tend to accept data\nthat confirms our beliefs"},{"time":940235,"text":"and reject data\nthat contradicts our beliefs."},{"time":944230,"text":"So evidence against our model,\nwe're likely to ignore,"},{"time":948189,"text":"even if it's compelling."},{"time":949461,"text":"It has to get very compelling\nbefore we'll pay attention."}]},{"cues":[{"time":953730,"text":"New models that extend\nlong periods of time are hard."},{"time":956351,"text":"Global warming is a great example."},{"time":958129,"text":"We're terrible at models\nthat span 80 years."},{"time":961595,"text":"We can do \"to the next harvest.\""},{"time":963682,"text":"We can often do \"until our kids grow up.\""},{"time":966500,"text":"But \"80 years,\" we're just not good at."},{"time":969715,"text":"So it's a very hard model to accept."},{"time":972739,"text":"We can have both models\nin our head simultaneously --"},{"time":976652,"text":"that kind of problem where\nwe're holding both beliefs together,"},{"time":983624,"text":"the cognitive dissonance."},{"time":985018,"text":"Eventually, the new model\nwill replace the old model."}]},{"cues":[{"time":988904,"text":"Strong feelings can create a model."},{"time":992151,"text":"September 11 created a security model\nin a lot of people's heads."},{"time":997538,"text":"Also, personal experiences\nwith crime can do it,"},{"time":1000850,"text":"personal health scare,"},{"time":1002253,"text":"a health scare in the news."},{"time":1004938,"text":"You'll see these called\n\"flashbulb events\" by psychiatrists."},{"time":1008923,"text":"They can create a model instantaneously,"},{"time":1011408,"text":"because they're very emotive."},{"time":1014648,"text":"So in the technological world,"},{"time":1016260,"text":"we don't have experience to judge models."},{"time":1019864,"text":"And we rely on others. We rely on proxies."},{"time":1022821,"text":"And this works, as long as\nit's the correct others."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1025923,"text":"We rely on government agencies"},{"time":1028629,"text":"to tell us what pharmaceuticals are safe."},{"time":1033057,"text":"I flew here yesterday."},{"time":1034994,"text":"I didn't check the airplane."},{"time":1037439,"text":"I relied on some other group"},{"time":1040058,"text":"to determine whether\nmy plane was safe to fly."},{"time":1042519,"text":"We're here, none of us fear the roof\nis going to collapse on us,"},{"time":1045841,"text":"not because we checked,"},{"time":1048070,"text":"but because we're pretty sure\nthe building codes here are good."},{"time":1053182,"text":"It's a model we just accept"},{"time":1056195,"text":"pretty much by faith."},{"time":1058071,"text":"And that's OK."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1062706,"text":"Now, what we want is people\nto get familiar enough with better models,"},{"time":1068603,"text":"have it reflected in their feelings,"},{"time":1070747,"text":"to allow them to make security trade-offs."},{"time":1074850,"text":"When these go out of whack,\nyou have two options."},{"time":1078593,"text":"One, you can fix people's feelings,\ndirectly appeal to feelings."},{"time":1082850,"text":"It's manipulation, but it can work."},{"time":1085913,"text":"The second, more honest way"},{"time":1088128,"text":"is to actually fix the model."},{"time":1091460,"text":"Change happens slowly."},{"time":1093585,"text":"The smoking debate took 40 years --\nand that was an easy one."},{"time":1099935,"text":"Some of this stuff is hard."},{"time":1102236,"text":"Really, though, information\nseems like our best hope."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1106016,"text":"And I lied."},{"time":1107312,"text":"Remember I said feeling, model, reality;\nreality doesn't change?"},{"time":1111356,"text":"It actually does."},{"time":1112755,"text":"We live in a technological world;"},{"time":1114493,"text":"reality changes all the time."},{"time":1117627,"text":"So we might have,\nfor the first time in our species:"},{"time":1120628,"text":"feeling chases model, model chases\nreality, reality's moving --"},{"time":1123835,"text":"they might never catch up."},{"time":1126920,"text":"We don't know."},{"time":1130354,"text":"But in the long term,"},{"time":1131981,"text":"both feeling and reality are important."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1134209,"text":"And I want to close with two quick\nstories to illustrate this."},{"time":1137466,"text":"1982 -- I don't know if people\nwill remember this --"},{"time":1139969,"text":"there was a short epidemic\nof Tylenol poisonings"},{"time":1143363,"text":"in the United States."},{"time":1144583,"text":"It's a horrific story."},{"time":1145968,"text":"Someone took a bottle of Tylenol,"},{"time":1148071,"text":"put poison in it, closed it up,\nput it back on the shelf,"},{"time":1151097,"text":"someone else bought it and died."},{"time":1152679,"text":"This terrified people."},{"time":1154376,"text":"There were a couple of copycat attacks."},{"time":1156627,"text":"There wasn't any real risk,\nbut people were scared."},{"time":1159496,"text":"And this is how the tamper-proof\ndrug industry was invented."},{"time":1163396,"text":"Those tamper-proof caps?\nThat came from this."},{"time":1165649,"text":"It's complete security theater."},{"time":1167244,"text":"As a homework assignment,\nthink of 10 ways to get around it."},{"time":1170159,"text":"I'll give you one: a syringe."},{"time":1172074,"text":"But it made people feel better."},{"time":1175484,"text":"It made their feeling of security\nmore match the reality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1180130,"text":"Last story: a few years ago,\na friend of mine gave birth."},{"time":1183088,"text":"I visit her in the hospital."},{"time":1184509,"text":"It turns out, when a baby's born now,"},{"time":1186456,"text":"they put an RFID bracelet on the baby,\na corresponding one on the mother,"},{"time":1190043,"text":"so if anyone other than the mother takes\nthe baby out of the maternity ward,"},{"time":1193687,"text":"an alarm goes off."},{"time":1194869,"text":"I said, \"Well, that's kind of neat."},{"time":1196622,"text":"I wonder how rampant\nbaby snatching is out of hospitals.\""},{"time":1200616,"text":"I go home, I look it up."},{"time":1201876,"text":"It basically never happens."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1203425,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1205293,"text":"But if you think about it,\nif you are a hospital,"},{"time":1208160,"text":"and you need to take a baby\naway from its mother,"},{"time":1210564,"text":"out of the room to run some tests,"},{"time":1212369,"text":"you better have some good\nsecurity theater,"},{"time":1214443,"text":"or she's going to rip your arm off."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1216412,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1218901,"text":"So it's important for us,"},{"time":1220642,"text":"those of us who design security,"},{"time":1222801,"text":"who look at security policy --"},{"time":1225686,"text":"or even look at public policy\nin ways that affect security."},{"time":1229746,"text":"It's not just reality;\nit's feeling and reality."},{"time":1233186,"text":"What's important"},{"time":1235075,"text":"is that they be about the same."},{"time":1236644,"text":"It's important that,\nif our feelings match reality,"},{"time":1239199,"text":"we make better security trade-offs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1241451,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1242628,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}